                <fr:title text="Quasi-compact schemes">Quasi-compact schemes</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  We say a <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">scheme</fr:link> is <html:em>quasi-compact</html:em> if its underlying space is <html:em>compact</html:em>.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>6</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>11</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-BH0E/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>schm-BH0E</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-BH0E/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Quasi-compact morphisms">Quasi-compact morphisms</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  More generally, we say a morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : Y \to  X]]></fr:tex> of <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">schemes</fr:link> is <html:em>quasi-compact</html:em>, if the underlying continuous map is <fr:link href="/topl-9BKS/" title="Quasi-compact continuous maps" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-9BKS/" display-uri="topl-9BKS" type="local">quasi-compact</fr:link>.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>6</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>16</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-826H/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>schm-826H</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-826H/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Quasi-compact morphisms are affine local">Quasi-compact morphisms are affine local</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  A map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> being <fr:link href="/schm-BH0E/" title="Quasi-compact morphisms" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-BH0E/" display-uri="schm-BH0E" type="local">quasi-compact</fr:link> is an <fr:link href="/schm-WURZ/" title="Affine local on the target" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-WURZ/" display-uri="schm-WURZ" type="local">affine local property on the target</fr:link>.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>16</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  It suffices to show that if there is an affine open cover <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A_i]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> that each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}(\operatorname {Spec} A_i)]]></fr:tex> is quasi-compact, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is quasi-compact. This is trivial, since this implies that each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}(\operatorname {Spec} A_i)]]></fr:tex> is covered by finitely many affine opens in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. 
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>6</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>17</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-5YJS/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>schm-5YJS</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-5YJS/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Quasi-compact morphisms are closed under pullback">Quasi-compact morphisms are closed under pullback</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/schm-BH0E/" title="Quasi-compact morphisms" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-BH0E/" display-uri="schm-BH0E" type="local">quasi-compact</fr:link> between schemes, then so is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Z \times _Y X \to  Z]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g : Z \to  Y]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> is an affine open in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Z]]></fr:tex>. For any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  g[U]]]></fr:tex>, choose an affine open <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V_y]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{g^{-1}(V_y)\}_{y\in  g[U]}]]></fr:tex> covers <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex>, which means there will be a finite subcover since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> is compact. This way, since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is quasi-compact, each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}(V_y)]]></fr:tex> is covered by finitely many affine opens <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigcup _{j_y}U_{j_y}]]></fr:tex>, which implies
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ (g^*f)^{-1}(U) \subseteq  U \times  \bigcup _{y,j_y}U_{j_y}, ]]></fr:tex>
  is a finite union of affine opens, hence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g^*f]]></fr:tex> is quasi-compact as well.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
