              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  Combining <fr:link href="/schm-826H/" title="Quasi-compact morphisms are affine local" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-826H/" display-uri="schm-826H" type="local">Proposition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-826H/" display-uri="schm-826H" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="/schm-5YJS/" title="Quasi-compact morphisms are closed under pullback" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-5YJS/" display-uri="schm-5YJS" type="local">Proposition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-5YJS/" display-uri="schm-5YJS" /></fr:link>, it follows that quasi-compact morphisms is an <fr:link href="/schm-NAP1/" title="Affine admissible classes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-NAP1/" display-uri="schm-NAP1" type="local">affine admissible class</fr:link>, since they are trivially also closed under compositions.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
