                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-55VG/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>schm-55VG</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-55VG/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Closed immersions are quasi-compact">Closed immersions are quasi-compact</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a scheme and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> a <fr:link href="/schm-JBRX/" title="Quasi-coherent ideals generate closed subschemes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-JBRX/" display-uri="schm-JBRX" type="local">closed subscheme</fr:link>. Then <fr:link href="/schm-FH0V/" title="Closed immersion" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-FH0V/" display-uri="schm-FH0V" type="local">closed immersion</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y \subseteq  X]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/schm-BH0E/" title="Quasi-compact morphisms" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-BH0E/" display-uri="schm-BH0E" type="local">quasi-compact</fr:link>. This follows trivially from general topology.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
